# QA — Protocol checks
- R4: Duplicate reply to same (target,locus,cqKey) is rejected (400/409).
- R5: Attack (WHY/GROUNDS) on surrendered/closed target is rejected (409).
- R7: After WHY→GROUNDS on φ, “Concede φ” is blocked; “Accept argument” (concede answer) is allowed.
- Self-guard: Authors cannot ask WHY of their own target; only authors may answer WHY.

# QA — Commitments
- CONCEDE produces (deliberationId, participantId, proposition, isRetracted=false).
- RETRACT flips isRetracted=true for that proposition.
- SSE: “dialogue:cs:refresh” fired on both, UI refreshes.

# QA — AF endpoint
- `/api/deliberations/[id]/dialectic` returns stable IN/OUT/UNDEC for preferred/grounded.
- Room toggle “asymmetric burden” flips some branches IN→OUT as expected.

